How to use tools to migrate data to ONTAP
Applies to
	• ONTAP 9
	• Data Migration

Description
A variety of NetApp tools and other options exist to aid in migrating data from external (both NetApp and non-NetApp) sources to ONTAP clusters. 

Procedure

NetApp Tools
NetApp provides the following options to assist with moving SAN and NAS workloads through storage-based solutions.

SAN Workloads
ONTAP Foreign LUN Import (FLI) provides both offline and online options for migrating SAN data from external sources.

NAS Workload
	• NetApp XCP enables fast and reliable any-to-NetApp and NetApp-to-NetApp data migrations and XCP file analytics provides visibility into the file system
	• SVM data mobility provides the ability to non-disruptively relocate an SVM from a source ONTAP cluster to a destination ONTAP cluster 
	• BlueXP Copy and Sync provides the ability to migrate NAS and Cloud provider data, S3, CIFS, NFS, Azure, AWS, Google cloud volumes

Application Options
Additional application based migration options can be used such as the following:
	• VMware Storage vMotion
	• Logical volume manager (LVM) based solutions
	• Utilities such as Rsync (Linux) and Robocopy (Windows)

Professional Services
Engaging NetApp Professional Services can assist with providing Data Migration Services.

Third Party Tools
Several third party tools are available that can help migrate data to ONTAP clusters such as Datadobi DobiMigrate.

